 helps enable the information age awarded by the president of the united states the medal of technology recognizes technological innovators who have made lasting contributions to americas competitiveness and standard of living among his many honors mr morgan is aÂ recipient of the prestigious ieee robert n noyce medal for his vision and leadership that transformed applied materials into an innovation leader and global partner for advancing microelectronics manufacturing technology he received the semiconductor industry association siaâ€™s robert n noyce award the associationâ€™s highest honor for outstanding achievement and leadership in support of the us semiconductor industry and the silicon valley leadership group spirit of silicon valley lifetime achievement award for his ethics community engagement and business successin  mr morgan was sworn in by president george w bush as vice chairman of the presidents export council the premier national advisory body on international trade he was appointed to the  usjapan private sector government commission and cochaired the sessions on corporate governance from  to  mr morgan served on the commission on uspacific trade and investment policy which advised president bill clinton and congress on steps the united states should take to achieve significant additional market access and improve trade relationships in the asiapacific region from  to  he served on the national advisory committee on semiconductors which advised president george h w bush and congress on a national strategy to strengthen competitiveness of the us semiconductor industrymr morgan has been recognized around the world for his leadership in the communityÂ as cofounders of the northern sierra partnership jim and his wife becky have focused their efforts on conserving biodiverse land in the california sierra nevada mountains he is active with the nature conservancy a global nonprofit organization which focuses on programs â€œprotecting nature and preserving lifeâ€ serving as a member of the board of directors past cochair of its asiapacific council and as a trustee of the nature conservancy of california mr morgan is an advisory board member for the center for science technology and society at santa clara university instrumental in the creation of the tech museum awards which launched in  mr morgan inspired the programâ€™s james c morgan global humanitarian award which honors individuals whose broad vision and leadership help address humanityâ€™s greatest challenges he formerly was a member of the board of directors of cisco systems inc from  to  and is director emeritus and past president of semiconductor equipment and materials international semi the first global trade association mr morgan is a past board member of the american electronics association aea the national center for apec asiapacific economic cooperation and of semisematech the association of us equipment companies which supplies advanced systems to the sematech chipmaking consortium mr morgan is a member of the world presidents organization from  to  he was a board member of joint venture silicon valley a leading community publicprivate collaborative from  to  he was cochairman of the japanwestern us association mr morgans contributions have been honored by many business education and community organizations throughout his careerselected awards accomplishments and honors   presentrobert n noyce medal  ieeespirit of silicon valley lifetime achievement award  silicon valley leadership grouprobert n noyce award  sianational medal of technology awarded by president bill clintonnamed one of the good ceos by businessweek magazine named one of the top  best ceos in america by worth magazinenamed one of the top  ceos by investors business dailythe ten most influential people in silicon valley san jose mercury newsinternational citizen of the year world forum of silicon valleyglobal humanitarian award the tech museum of innovationglobal pioneer award semiconduct