 released on april   james is also well known for her numerous musical collaborations with the jazz collective postmodern jukebox contents  early life and education  career  personal life  discography  studio albums  cover albums  singles  references  external links early life and educationedit james was born morgan grunerud in boise idaho the daughter of educators and actors allen grunerud and shellie harwood the family moved frequently when james was a child going from pocatello idaho to utah tennessee and eventually modesto california where she spent her high school years she has a younger brother nicholas who is an avantgarde musician and comedian james was inspired by her actor parents to enter the performing arts and she joined a choir while in middle school her grandmother also bought her a karaoke machine and agreed to pay for singing lessons until james went to college james attended high school at peter johansen high school in modesto and graduated in  at the age of  james realized it was her dream to attend the juilliard school in new york city and after auditioning she was eventually waitlisted and then rejected however after significant correspondence with the head of admissions she convinced him to accept her as the classs seventh singer one above the usual six there she studied opera and eventually earned her bachelor of music in voice in  in college james also took a master class headed by broadway veteran barbara cook careeredit after college james initially struggled to find work and looked for jobs that utilized both her operatic and classical training james did not make her broadway debut until  in the musical production of the addams family starring nathan lane and bebe neuwirth in  james appeared in frank wildhorns wonderland and the broadway revival of godspell james sprained her ankle in a rehearsal for godspell in october  and was unable to perform during previews she recuperated and by november  was performing in the musical at the circle in the square theatre in  james took on the role of teena marie in motown the musical she stayed with the cast until december  when she left to pursue a vocal performance tour while broadway she moonlighted as a solo artist with a backing band often composed of chris fenwick matt fieldes damien bassman among others she has played at numerous new york city clubs including le poisson rouge  below rockwood music hall and birdland her first solo album morgan james live a celebration of nina simone was recorded at new york jazz club dizzys and is a collection of nina simone cover songs it was released via epic records in december  her second solo album and first studio album hunter was recorded in  and released via epic records in june  the track album was produced by doug wamble and is james first album of all solo material the album included her cover of princes song call my name which prince allowed her to put on the record on december   james released her second cover album blue released on the th anniversary of joni mitchells album of the same name reckless abandon her second solo studio album will be independently released on april   via her selfcreated hedonist records it is her first album to feature completely original material and heavily incorporates elements of soul and rb on march   she embarked on a national headlining spring reckless abandon tour in support of the album since  james collaborates with postmodern jukebox producing several cover songs on their youtube channel and joining them on tour personal lifeedit james currently lives in harlem with her husband guitarist and producer doug wamble whom she wed in spring of  discographyedit studio albumsedit title album details hunter released november   us label epic reckless abandon released april   us label hedonist records cover albumsedit title album details morgan james live a celebration of nina simone released december   us label epic blue released december   us label certified morganic singlesedit year single album  call my name na referencesedit  a b c holden stephen  june  emoting and belting from holiday to prince the new york times retrieved  september Â   gioia michael  september  playbill playlist motown actress and soul singer morgan james shares her musical inspirations playbill retrieved  september Â   cerasaro pat  august  new morgan james single call my name now available broadway world retrieved  september Â   a b victor greg  june  the summer of â€²s first â€˜musthaveâ€™ album morgan jamesâ€™ hunterâ€™ parcbench retrieved  september Â   a b c collar matt  june  review by matt collar allmusic retrieved  september Â   a b c millegan renner lisa  may  johansen high grad enjoying kooky spooky role in broadway show the modesto bee retrieved  september Â   a b c d gans andrew  february  diva talk chatting with godspell star morgan james playbill retrieved  september Â   a b c d e f g h bialas michael  april  first listen with reckless abandon morgan james bares her soul power the huffington post the huffington post retrieved  april Â   a b rowland marijke  april  modestoâ€™s morgan james â€˜on fireâ€™ joins cabaret the modesto bee retrieved  september Â   hodges bruce may  james and dinnerstein release new song cds the juilliard journal retrieved  september Â   a b c wonderlands morgan james plays concert at birdland  broadway world  may  retrieved  september Â   a b gans andrew  october  morgan james temporarily sidelined from godspell free concert set for oct  playbill retrieved  september Â   blank matt  december  photo exclusive a threeshow day with godspells morgan james playbill retrieved  september Â   a b gans andrew  october  addams familys james to offer solo concert in november playbill retrieved  september Â   a b collar matt  december  review by matt collar allmusic retrieved  september Â   a b c cakes b  january  morgan james pays homage to joni mitchellâ€™s â€˜blueâ€™  preps for upcoming â€˜reckless abandon tourâ€™ soulbounce retrieved  a